sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant FE as React Frontend
    participant CC as CommentController
    participant CS as CommentService
    participant DB as PostgreSQL

    User->>FE: Click Upvote on comment
    FE->>FE: Check: vote === "UPVOTE"? removing = true/false
    FE->>CC: POST /api/comments/{id}/vote { voteType: "UPVOTE" }
    CC->>CS: voteComment(commentId, userId, UPVOTE)
    CS->>DB: SELECT * FROM comments WHERE id=? FOR UPDATE
    Note over DB: Pessimistic write lock acquired
    DB-->>CS: Comment row (locked)
    CS->>CS: Check author.id != userId (no self-vote)
    CS->>DB: SELECT * FROM comment_votes\nWHERE comment_id=? AND user_id=?
    DB-->>CS: Existing vote (or null)

    alt No existing vote
        CS->>DB: INSERT INTO comment_votes (UPVOTE, user_id, comment_id)
        CS->>DB: UPDATE comments SET score = score+1
        CS->>DB: UPDATE users SET score = score+5.0 WHERE id=author_id
    else Same vote (toggle off)
        CS->>DB: DELETE FROM comment_votes WHERE id=?
        CS->>DB: UPDATE comments SET score = score-1
        CS->>DB: UPDATE users SET score = score-5.0 WHERE id=author_id
    else Opposite vote (flip)
        CS->>DB: UPDATE comment_votes SET vote_type=UPVOTE
        CS->>DB: UPDATE comments SET score = score+2
        CS->>DB: UPDATE users SET score = score+7.5 WHERE id=author_id
        CS->>DB: UPDATE users SET score = score+1.5 WHERE id=voter_id
    end

    Note over DB: Lock released on commit
    CS-->>CC: Updated Comment entity
    CC-->>FE: 200 CommentResponse { score, userVote, authorScore }
    FE->>FE: Update score display optimistically
    FE-->>User: Vote button highlighted, score updated
